Note that, as mentioned in the specification, this code has a bug. The calculation `num * num` is not the correct way to raise a number to a power. A correct implementation would use the `pow` function or a loop to calculate the power. For example:
```
#include <iostream>
#include <cmath>

using namespace std;

int main() {
    double num, p;
    cout << "Enter a number: ";
    cin >> num;
    cout << "Enter the power to which the number should be raised: ";
    cin >> p;
    cout << num << " raised to the power of " << p << " is " << pow(num, p) << endl;
